/*!
\page discode_06_refreshedtriggered_sequencereader Move one of the components to another thread
 
\section ts_description Description
Modify the TriggeredSequenceViewer.xml in order to add the displayed image refreshment.

\section ts_structure Task structure
The structure of the RefreshedTriggeredSequenceViewer task is shown below.

\htmlonly
<img src="images/RefreshedTriggeredSequenceViewer.png" style="margin: 5px; width: 600px;" alt="RefreshedTriggeredSequenceViewer"/>
\endhtmlonly

\section ts_file Task file
Create a new RefreshedTriggeredSequenceViewer.xml file on the base of the previously created TriggeredSequenceViewer.xml.
Modify required parts:
- Move the <b>CvWindow</b> component to a separate <b>Thread3</b> thread.  
\code
	<Components>
		...
		<Window type="CvWindow" thread="Thread3" group="s1">
			<title>Preview</title>	
		</Window>
		...
\endcode

- Create another executor and set the main thread component to <b>Window</b>. 
\code
	<Executors>
		...
		<Thread3 type="periodic">
			<main_component>Window</main_component>
			<interval>0.2</interval>
 		</Thread3>
		...
\endcode
\note Note that the new executor is "periodic", thus require an additional parameter (interval, in seconds) to be set. 

\section ts_result Result
A sequence of images  will be displayed. After an image will be shown application will wait for user 
to enter the 't' (must be followed by <enter>) to load and display another. Besides displayed 
images will be refreshed.

\section ts_sections Related sections
\see \ref manuals_components : Description of components
\see \ref manuals_executors : Description of executors
\see \ref CvWindow : Sink responsible for displaying images

\prevnext{discode_05_trigerred_sequencereader,discode_07_component_images_sharpener}
*/